# Form Enter / Send submit

Every user-facing **form** or **form-like flow** (dialog, sheet, inline save row with text input + primary action) must submit when the user presses **Enter** on desktop or **Send** on mobile.

## Required pattern

1. Wrap submit-capable inputs and the primary action in a native `<form>`.
2. Handle submit with `onSubmit`; call `preventDefaultFormSubmit` from `@/lib/client/form-enter-submit.shared` when using JS handlers.
3. Primary action uses `type="submit"` (not `type="button"` + `onClick` alone).
4. Set `enterKeyHint={FORM_SUBMIT_ENTER_KEY_HINT}` on the **last** submit-capable text/email/password/number input in the flow (shows **Send** on mobile).

```tsx
import {
  FORM_SUBMIT_ENTER_KEY_HINT,
  preventDefaultFormSubmit,
} from "@/lib/client/form-enter-submit.shared";

<form
  onSubmit={(event) => {
    preventDefaultFormSubmit(event);
    void save();
  }}
>
  <input enterKeyHint={FORM_SUBMIT_ENTER_KEY_HINT} … />
  <button type="submit" disabled={busy}>Save</button>
</form>
```

## Textareas

- Use `enterKeyHint={FORM_SUBMIT_ENTER_KEY_HINT}` for mobile Send.
- Desktop: **Enter** submits, **Shift+Enter** newline — wire `onKeyDown` with `handleTextareaEnterSubmit` from the same module.
- Opt out per control with `data-no-enter-submit` on a wrapper.

## Inline / table cells

Mini-forms per row are fine (`<form onSubmit={…}>` around input + Save). Do not rely on ad-hoc `onKeyDown` unless a native form is impossible.

## Out of scope

- Debounced search/filter-only inputs (no submit action).
- File-only pickers.
- Button-only wizard steps with no text fields.
- `<select>` / checkbox-only rows where Enter semantics are ambiguous.

## Checklist for new/changed UI

- [ ] Input + primary button wrapped in `<form onSubmit>`
- [ ] Submit button is `type="submit"`
- [ ] Last text input has `enterKeyHint="send"`
- [ ] Textarea uses Shift+Enter for newline if multi-line copy is needed
